text.tspan: Typical Residential Solar: Tied to Grid & $$$
Small-scale Solar: Lower Cost & More Resilient
- Goal: reduce electricity costs, generate elecricity 'renewably'
- Converts low-voltage, DC power from panels to high-voltage AC power
- This AC power is used for household appliances, or sold back to the grid
- Usually no battery backup; if grid fails, no power
- Need access to / ownership of roof
- Goal: meet core electricity needs independent of grid
- Can opt for DC appliances (no inverter needed)
- Battery backup is easy, inexpensive, and scalable
- Wiring is simple and quite safe; easy to DIY
- Smaller systems can fit on apartment balcony
